description: {"blocks":[{"key":"1c9rr","text":"Microscopy-based evaluation of Parkin translocation and mitophagy in FBXO7-/- cell lines","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We are still developing and optimizing this protocol

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"coho3","text":"Wash HeLa cells expressing GFP-Parkin with 1x PBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8732p","text":"Add Trypsin to cells for 5 min and incubate at 37°C to dissociate cells from plastic well","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e9pth","text":"Resuspend cells in 1 mL DMEM media","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bd5i","text":"Count cells","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fkie4","text":"Seed appropriate number of cells into 24-well glass bottom dish","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ig9c","text":"Top up glass bottom dish with either 1 mL DMEM and place cells back into incubator","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9puig","text":"Induce mitophagy using Antimycin A / Oligomycin A for the desired time.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2q3rn","text":"Aspirate DMEM and fix cells in 1 ml pre-warmed 4% PFA for 30 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5eopv","text":"Aspirate PFA solution and wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5sal3","text":"Permeabilize the cells by adding 0.2% Triton X-100 in PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cchmr","text":"Remove the detergent solution by aspiration.  Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3a4he","text":"Block cells for 10 min with 3% BSA – 1x PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"54gmg","text":"Remove BSA solution by aspiration.  Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9g82k","text":"Incubate with primary antibodies in 3% BSA - 1x PBS for 3h at RT with gentle shaking.  a.     Anti-GFP (chicken)  b.     Anti-HSP60 (mouse)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"d3kcs","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bf8gn","text":"Incubate with secondary antibodies in 3% BSA - 1x PBS for 45 min – 1h.  a.     Goat anti-chicken AlexaFlour 488  b.     Goat anti-mouse AlexaFluor 647  c.     DNA-SPY555","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cs8ai","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e660s","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"be4ti","text":"Exchange PBST with 1x PBS and keep cells at 4°C until imaging. Image within the next few days.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cche","text":"Mount glass bottom plate on Yokogawa CSU-W1 spinning disk confocal on a Nikon Eclipse Ti-E motorized microscope equipped with a Nikon Apochromat 60×/1.42 N.A oil-objective lens. Image signals of 488/568/647 fluorophores in sequential manner with a Nikon LUN-F XL solid state laser combiner ([laser line – laser power]: 488 - 80mW, 561 - 65mW, 640nm - 60mW]) using a Semrock Di01-T405/488/568/647 dichroic mirror. Fluorescence emissions were collected with 488 Chroma ET525/50m [488 nm], 568 Chroma ET605/52m [561 nm], 633 Chroma ET705/72m [640 nm] filters, respectively (Chroma Technologies) using NIS-Elements image acquisition software. Consistent laser intensity and exposure times must be maintained for all samples. Acquire 8 µm z-stacks for each image.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3vgi2","text":"Image adequate number of cells per repeat in each condition.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9f16m","text":"Perform image quantification was in your tool of choice. Here we will use CellProfiler and segmentation pipelines can be found online (https://github.com/harperlaboratory/FBXO7).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"27sq0","text":"Export results and plot in your tool of choice for graphing and statistical analysis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
